<subSubSection id="C1EE6CEDFFB0FFBFFF5A009FFD02BF3B" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB0FFBFFF5A009FFE9AB9A7" blockId="59.[189,310,896,922]" box="[189,310,896,922]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<heading id="D203880AFFB0FFBFFF5A009FFE9AB9A7" bold="true" box="[189,310,896,922]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" reason="3">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFF5A009FFE9AB9A7" bold="true" box="[189,310,896,922]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB0FFBFFF5A00B0FD02BF3B" blockId="59.[188,1401,943,1286]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Distinguished from most species of 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFD8000AFFD6AB9F4" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" box="[615,710,944,969]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFD8000AFFD6AB9F4" box="[615,710,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Voconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pale membranal veins. This species is most similar to two other 
<collectingRegion id="4B30F184FFB0FFBFFEBE00CDFE15B9D1" box="[345,441,978,1004]" country="Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Oriental</collectingRegion>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFDCD00CCFD1DB9D1" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[554,689,978,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFDCD00CCFD1DB9D1" box="[554,689,978,1004]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">V. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB0FFBFFD5E00CCFCB9B9D0" box="[697,789,979,1005]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFCB200CCFC71B9D1" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[853,989,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFCB200CCFC71B9D1" box="[853,989,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">V. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB0FFBFFC0300CCFBEDB9D0" box="[996,1089,979,1005]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It is distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFF5800E9FEE8BE32" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[191,324,1013,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFF5800E9FEE8BE32" box="[191,324,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">V. decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB0FFBFFEAE00E9FE0FBE2D" box="[329,419,1014,1040]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by its distribution in 
<collectingRegion id="4B30F184FFB0FFBFFD7900EAFCA8BE32" box="[670,772,1013,1039]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
; the dark brown, almost black coloration of the body; and uniformly brown scutellum. 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFDDA0706FD7CBE0F" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[573,720,1048,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lirophleps" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFDDA0706FD7CBE0F" box="[573,720,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">V. lirophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB0FFBFFD300706FC9DBE0E" box="[727,817,1049,1075]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is about 
<quantity id="4E0C9283FFB0FFBFFC7C0706FC72BE0E" box="[923,990,1049,1075]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
shorter than 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB0FFBFFB900706FB50BE0F" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[1143,1276,1049,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFB900706FB50BE0F" box="[1143,1276,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">V. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB0FFBFFAE30706FAF2BE0E" box="[1284,1374,1049,1075]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It is also distinguishable by the yellow spots adjacent to the lateral ocellar margin; slightly more globose head (about 1.2 times as long as wide); pedicel much shorter (about 1.1 times length of head width); maxillary plates converge in dorsal view, postocular region is shorter than eye; narrow pronotal collar; short anterior pronotal lobe relative to posterior pronotal lobe (about 2.2 times shorter than posterior lobe); conspicuous distal yellow spot on the corium; and only three large spines and two small spines on the posterior row of spines of the hind leg.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1EE6CEDFFB0FFBFFF5A0632FCA5BF81" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB0FFBFFF5A0632FEE8BF7A" blockId="59.[189,324,1325,1351]" box="[189,324,1325,1351]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<heading id="D203880AFFB0FFBFFF5A0632FEE8BF7A" bold="true" box="[189,324,1325,1351]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" reason="3">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFF5A0632FEE8BF7A" bold="true" box="[189,324,1325,1351]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB0FFBFFF5A0643FCA5BF81" blockId="59.[189,1399,1372,1469]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Derived from the Latinized Greek prefix ‘ 
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFD430643FD7BBF4B" box="[676,727,1372,1398]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">liro-</emphasis>
’ meaning ‘pale’ combined with the Latinized Greek noun ‘ 
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB0FFBFFF200660FEB8BFA4" box="[199,276,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">phleps</emphasis>
’ meaning ‘vein’. Refers to the prominent pale coloration of the membranal veins. To be treated as a noun in apposition, ending not to be changed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
