<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB7FFB8FF5A06B7FE83BFFF" blockId="60.[189,303,1448,1474]" box="[189,303,1448,1474]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="D203880AFFB7FFB8FF5A06B7FE83BFFF" bold="true" box="[189,303,1448,1474]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="3">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FF5A06B7FE83BFFF" bold="true" box="[189,303,1448,1474]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="894B3F66FFB7FFB8FF5A06C8FBA0BC67" blockId="60.[189,1398,1495,1627]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Despite the 
<typeStatus id="564F81C4FFB7FFB8FEA906C8FE6CBFCC" box="[334,448,1495,1521]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB7FFB8FE0A06C7FDDABFCC" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[493,630,1496,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FE0A06C7FDDABFCC" box="[493,630,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">V. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB7FFB8FD9806C8FD71BFCC" box="[639,733,1495,1521]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB7FFB8FCFC06C7FC1CBFCC" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[795,944,1495,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lirophleps" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FCFC06C7FC1CBFCC" box="[795,944,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">V. lirophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB7FFB8FC5D06C8FBB4BFCC" box="[954,1048,1495,1521]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
being collected within about 
<quantity id="4E0C9283FFB7FFB8FF5A06E5FEB7BC29" box="[189,283,1530,1556]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="km" value="106.0">106 km</quantity>
of each other, there are several differences, particularly in size. Among our larger series, conspecific 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB7FFB8FEAD0501FE05BC0A" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" box="[330,425,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FEAD0501FE05BC0A" box="[330,425,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Voconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males do not vary much in size, and 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB7FFB8FC880501FBAFBC0A" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[879,1027,1565,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lirophleps" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FC880501FBAFBC0A" box="[879,1027,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">V. lirophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB7FFB8FBEC0501FBCBBC05" box="[1035,1127,1566,1592]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is about 
<quantity id="4E0C9283FFB7FFB8FB310502FAB0BC05" box="[1238,1308,1565,1592]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
shorter than 
<taxonomicName id="4EF444E5FFB7FFB8FF10055EFED1BC67" authority="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch, 2022" authorityName="Castillo &amp; Rédei &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2022" box="[247,381,1601,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Voconia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coronata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BB80E374FFB7FFB8FF10055EFED1BC67" box="[247,381,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">V. coronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0B35E0FFFB7FFB8FE63055EFE4EBC66" box="[388,482,1601,1627]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; thus, we are keeping them as separate species.
</paragraph>
